{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did not hear from them for a while.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I actually found out they were deported, because once they were deported, they were deported-- they were not sent to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would deport Jews at the time to Poland, to anywhere, just to get them out of Germany or Austria.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My parents were deported beginning of 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With my brother, right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were sent to a town in Poland called Opole, O-P-O-L-E.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have subsequently found out, providing through the Austrian government, as to what-- I knew exactly what transport was, because I found that out after the war by doing a certain amount of research.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But once they arrived there, they were able to still communicate to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I was still able to receive letters, and that's how I know they were deported from Austria into Poland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're approximately at the beginning of 1941, January, February, when they were deported.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think the first letter I started getting again was in March or April of 1941.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I started communicating with them again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At first, when they were deported, my father would write, and my mother would always add something on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother would write a few words also.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After a while, I-- my brother no longer wrote anything on there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the last letter I got from my parents, which was on the day of my bar mitzvah after I came to the United States, which I will-- I will read it later on-- only my father wrote.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I am very positive that my father-- my brother and my mother were already dead at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father must have been killed shortly afterwards.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
